▪ 01 : Modify GRUB's kernel/linux(16) command.
▪ 02 : Modify the args to GRUB's initrd command.
▪ 03 : Modify kernel's root parameter.
▪ 04 : Rename GRUB v1 or v2 config files to <FILE>.old allowing for quick recovery.
▪ 05 : Remove initrd line from GRUBv1 and GRUBv2 config files.
▪ 06 : Destroy GRUBv1 or GRUBv2 stage 1 in MBR.
▪ 07 : Destroy GRUBv1 stage 2 img file in /boot/grub.
▪ 21 : Put typo in selinux/config to cause missing policy kernel panic.
▪ 22 : Reserve a ton of RAM via memmap kernel parameter & vm.min_free_kbytes sysctl.
▪ 23 : Rename a swap LV and change fstab reference (UUID, LABEL, or path) to an altogether different name but don't fix kernel cmdline.
▪ 24 : Remove execute bit from all the things.
▪ 25 : Create LVM snapshot of rootdev and remove dm-snapshot.ko from initrd/initramfs. (Since we can't count on free extents in VG, reduce swap LV to make space.)
▪ 26 : Preallocate all RAM to hugepages via sysctl and kernel cmdline.
▪ 27 : Configure LVM filter to ignore all PVs matching [vhs]d & rebuild initrd/initramfs.
